  "description": "This test case evaluates the ability to identify patients with depression diagnoses using ICD-9 and ICD-10 codes. The phenotype requires complex longitudinal analysis with a 2/30/180 rule (evidence on at least 2 distinct days, 30-180 days apart), but this query focuses on the core diagnosis identification component. It should capture the three severity types mentioned in the phenotype: depression with psychosis (most severe), major depressive disorder, and non-major depressive disorder.",
